---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import { SITE, CURRENT_FOCUS } from "../consts";
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description={`Release notes`} contained>
  <article class="grid grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)] gap-10">
    <header class="grid gap-[0.85rem] pb-8 border-b border-border">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>{SITE.author}</h1>
      <p class="lede">Software Engineer</p>
    </header>

    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I build AI-native products and the systems that keep them legible. My
        work sits at the point where architecture, tooling, and interface
        decisions start to determine real product quality — and I prefer to
        document that work the way I think about it: as engineering reference,
        not marketing.
      </p>

      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        Good software stays understandable under pressure. Product surfaces
        should remain calm when the systems beneath them grow complex,
        asynchronous, or operationally noisy. I favor interfaces and
        architectures that a new engineer can reason about, and AI features that
        meaningfully improve decisions rather than decorate the product with
        novelty.
      </p>
      <p>
        Writing things down is part of the method. If I cannot explain the shape
        of a problem or the tradeoffs behind a solution, I usually do not
        understand it well enough yet. This site is where that thinking is made
        visible — one specification and one post-mortem at a time.
      </p>

      <h2>Technical focus</h2>
      <ul>
        {CURRENT_FOCUS.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
      </ul>
      <p>
        Most of the work lands between engineering and product: AI-native
        workflows and agents, frontend systems and performance, observability,
        and practical architecture choices made under real constraints.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
